A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Libraries – State Policy – Alterations
3 FOR the purpose of altering the State standards for libraries and the State policy for local
4 school systems operating school library media programs to clarify that programming
5 offered by a library or library media program is among the library services that must
6 be made available to all persons a library serves; and generally relating to the State
7 standards for libraries.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
9 Article – Education
10 Section 4–142(a) and 23–102.1(b)
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Education
16 4–142.
17 (a) It is the policy of the State that each local school system operate its school
18 library media program consistent with the following standards:
19 (1) The materials, services, [and] resources, AND PROGRAMMING
20 provided in a school library media program are provided for the interest, information, and
21 instructional support of students and school personnel of the schools the program serves;
